Description: AI-powered command assistant using local LLMs
 osh (Oh Shell!) translates natural language descriptions into executable
 Linux/shell commands using local LLMs via Ollama.
 .
 Describe what you want in plain English and get multiple command
 alternatives with detailed, line-by-line explanations — no cloud
 required, no man-page diving.
 .
 Features:
  - Multiple command alternatives per query, each fully explained
  - Built-in QA safety review (PASS / WARN / MISS / FAIL verdicts)
  - Checks command availability before suggesting tools
  - Detects available scripting languages (bash, awk, python, perl, …)
  - Copy commands to clipboard or execute directly
  - Companion 'ask' tool for general-purpose Q&A
  - XDG-compliant paths and daily logging
  - Supports thinking models (deepseek-r1, etc.)
 .
 Note: requires Ollama (https://ollama.com) installed separately.
